burn(uint256).details: Burns `tokenId`. See {ERC721-_burn}. Requirements: - The caller must own `tokenId` or be an approved operator.

onCall((bytes,address,uint256),address,u.details: This function is called by the Gateway contract upon receiving a message.      If the destination is ZetaChain, mint an NFT and set its URI.      If the destination is another chain, swap the gas token for the corresponding      ZRC-20 token and use the Gateway to send a message to mint an NFT on the      destination chain.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setConnected(address,bytes).details: Can only be called by the contract owner.

setGasLimit(uint256).details: Can only be called by the contract owner.

setGateway(address).details: Can only be called by the contract owner.

params.gatewayAddress: The address of the gateway contract.

transferCrossChain(uint256,address,addre.details: This function accepts native ZETA tokens as gas fees, which are swapped      for the corresponding ZRC-20 gas token of the destination chain. The NFT is then      transferred to the destination chain using the ZetaChain Gateway.

params.destination: Address of the ZRC-20 gas token for the destination chain.
params.receiver: Address of the recipient on the destination chain.
params.tokenId: The ID of the NFT to transfer.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

onAbort((bytes,address,uint256,bool,uint.notice: onAbort is executed when a transfer from one connected chain to another fails inside onCall, for example, because the amount of tokens supplied is not sufficient to cover the withdraw gas fee to the destination and also not enough to cover withdraw gas fee to the source chain. In this scenario we don't have enough tokens to send NFT cross-chain, so the best thing we can do is to transfer the NFT to the original sender on ZetaChain.

onRevert((address,address,uint256,bytes).notice: Handles a cross-chain call failure and reverts the NFT transfer.

setConnected(address,bytes).notice: Links a ZRC-20 gas token address to an NFT contract         on the corresponding chain.

setGasLimit(uint256).notice: Sets the gas limit for cross-chain transfers.

setGateway(address).notice: Sets the ZetaChain gateway contract address.

transferCrossChain(uint256,address,addre.notice: Transfers an NFT to a connected chain.
